913. As the elder son he carried his father's first name forward into the next generation and into his own World War II service. His mother Bertha would remarry Silas Young twelve years later in 1925, giving him Young half-siblings when he was already nineteen."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Five children scattered across America in turn","body":"Freeman Wilbur and Minerva McKinnon had at least five known children born 1925 to 1933: daughters Ruth and Ruby, sons James Donald (Korean War Navy veteran), Robert (Navy veteran), and Leroy 'Lee.' James eventually moved to Texas where he died in Killeen in 2015. The other siblings remained in Crawford County Pennsylvania."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"freeman-lybarger-1906"},"I00676":{"id":"I00676","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Minerva","middle_name":"Irene","last_name":"Lybarger","maiden_name":"McKinnon","married_names":[],"extra_names":"Irene McKinnon Lybarger","gender":"female","display_name":"Minerva Irene McKinnon Lybarger"},"birth":{"country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD4281","location_state":"Pennsylvania","location_country":"United States","children_ids":["HD4283","HD4284","HD4285","HD4286","HD4287"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["pennsylvania_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"minerva-mckinnon"},"I00671":{"id":"I00671","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Freeman","middle_name":"Delbert","last_name":"Lybarger","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Freeman Delbert Lybarger"},"birth":{"year":1874,"month":4,"day":14,"city":"Fairfield","county":"Swift County","state":"Minnesota","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1913,"month":9,"day":20,"city":"Warren","county":"Warren County","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM339","plot_notes":"Greendale Cemetery, Meadville Crawford County PA — with father-in-law Harmon Unger's Greendale-buried Ellis-Unger family."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{},"number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD4276","date_year":1902,"location_state":"Pennsylvania","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death","end_year":1913,"children_ids":["HD4281","HD4282","HD4296"]}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["minnesota_migration","pennsylvania_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Minnesota-born like his wife's late father Harmon","body":"Freeman Delbert Lybarger was born April 14, 1874 in Fairfield Swift County Minnesota — by uncanny coincidence the same state where his wife Bertha's father Harmon Demmington Unger had been born seventeen years earlier. Both Minnesota-born men migrated east to Crawford County Pennsylvania, married into the Ellis-Unger family, and died young in Pennsylvania. Freeman died at thirty-nine in Warren PA on September 20, 1913."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"freeman-lybarger-1874"},"HD4276":{"id":"HD4276","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":true,"bio":{"first_name":"Bertha","middle_name":"Mae","last_name":"Young","maiden_name":"Unger","married_names":["Lybarger","Young"],"gender":"female","display_name":"Bertha Mae Unger Young"},"birth":{"year":1884,"month":12,"day":15,"city":"Meadville","county":"Crawford County","state":"Pennsylvania","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1959,"month":3,"day":19,"city":"Hollywood","county":"Broward County","state":"Florida","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM339","plot_notes":"Greendale Cemetery, Meadville Crawford County PA — body returned from Florida."},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"generation_from_thomas":10,"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_paths_to_thomas":1,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"parents":{"father_id":"I00668","mother_id":"HD4273"},"number_of_marriages":2,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"I00671","date_year":1902,"location_state":"Pennsylvania","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1913,"children_ids":["HD4281","HD4282","HD4296"],"spouse_research_notes":"Freeman Delbert Lybarger (I00671, 1874 MN - 1913 PA). Two confirmed sons: Freeman Wilbur Lybarger (1906-1988, WWII vet), Irvin Clarence Lybarger (1908-1973). Per Gertrude Winger's 2014 obit there may have been additional siblings: 'Chester, Irvin, and Wilbur Lybarger' — Chester (and possibly others) to be researched. Children built later stages."},{"marriage_number":2,"spouse_id":"I00672","date_year":1925,"location_state":"Pennsylvania","location_country":"United States","end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1953,"children_ids":["HD4288","HD4297","HD4298","HD4299","HD4300","HD4301","HD4302","HD4303","HD4304","HD4305"],"spouse_research_notes":"Silas Howard Young (I00672, 1873-1953). Multiple children — confirmed Gertrude Virginia Young Winger (1926-2014); per Gertrude's obit also Joseph, Noble, Leah, Austin, Reno, David Young, Lois Stanley, Paul Young, Dortha Free. Children to be built later stages."}],"education":[],"career":[],"military_service":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["pennsylvania_migration","florida_migration"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"family","header":"Twice widowed, ended life far from home","body":"Bertha Mae Unger was widowed twice — first when Freeman Delbert Lybarger died in 1913 at thirty-nine, then when second husband Silas Howard Young died in 1953 after twenty-eight years of marriage. She moved south to Florida in her later years and died in Hollywood Broward County in 1959 at seventy-four. Her body was returned to Meadville and buried at Greendale Cemetery."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Two husbands, many children across both marriages","body":"Bertha's first marriage to Freeman Lybarger produced at least two confirmed sons before his 1913 death — Freeman Wilbur (1906) and Irvin Clarence (1908). Her second marriage to Silas Young in 1925 produced multiple Young children including Gertrude Virginia born 1926. Per a later family obituary at least ten siblings spanned the two marriages — many remain unbuilt pending research."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"bertha-young-1884"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":{},"crossConnections":[]}